    "section": "Selection",
    "slides": [
        {
            "id": "s_l2_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "The Hook 🪝",
            "content": "To change something on the page (like a header), you first need to **select** it.\n\nThe most powerful way is `document.querySelector()`."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l2_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "Which method finds the first match?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "find()",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "querySelector()",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt3",
                        "text": "select()",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "`querySelector` returns the first matching element."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_3",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "CSS Selectors 🎨",
            "content": "It uses the same selectors as CSS!\n\n* `querySelector('h1')` finds the first `<h1>`.\n* `querySelector('.btn')` finds the first with class `btn`.\n* `querySelector('#main')` finds the ID `main`."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_4",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Example 🔎",
            "content": "Let's grab the main title.",
            "codeSnippet": "// HTML: <h1 id=\"title\">Hello</h1>\n\nlet title = document.querySelector('#title');\nconsole.log(title);",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": false
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l2_5",
